  "text": "Next, from our optical spectra [CITATION_1] Table 1 . And then, from relation (1) we may derive the black hole masses for these values of * ; see Table 2 . Our optical spectra of the Mrk261/262 are obtained on the 6 m telescope at Special Astrophysical Observatory of Russia, with the Universal Astronomical Grating Spectrograph. The detector was a 530 × 580, 18 × 24 m pixel CCD, and the spectral band was (3720Å) − (7150Å). The hz44 standard star was chosen for flux calibration, and the spectral dispersion was 5.9Å/pix. The resolution, as measured on the night sky lines, was ∼16.3Å (FWHM). In [CITATION_2] , we also used the observational data of Mrk 266, obtained on the 5 m Hale telescope at Palomar Observatory with the Norris Spectrograph. Rotating the position angle by 45 degrees, each component was observed in red and blue parts at different position angles of 31 ∘ , 76 ∘ , 121 ∘ , and 166 ∘ . The pixel scale of detector was 1024 × 256 pixels for red part and 180 × 800 pixels for blue part. The exposure times amounted to 900 s for each spectrum in case of position angle 31",
